    <h1><strong>Fun with Formatting in HTML!</strong></h1>
    <p><strong>Bold text</strong> is often used for <u>emphasis</u>. 
        It's important to note that <em>italic text</em> can add a <small>subtle</small> touch to your writing. 
        Using <mark>marked text</mark> highlights key points, making them stand out.</p>
        <hr>
        <p>As you continue reading, you'll notice that combining these elements creates a visually engaging experience. 
        Remember, the key to good formatting is to use these features <u>sparingly</u>, 
        and <em>meaningfully</em>. Occasionally, <del>overusing</del> 
        <u>appropriately using</u> these tags ensures the content remains clear and effective.</p>
